    "Electroweak observables.In this category, we include Z-and W -pole measurements, lepton flavor universality (LFU) tests in τ -decays, and flavor-conserving Higgs decays.• As far as measurements at the Z-and W -pole are concerned, we include all the observables listed in tables 1 and 2 of ref.",
    "[33], using the SM predictions and experimental values given therein, as well as the same G F, m Z, and α EM input scheme.",
    "We do not include the latest CDF II result on m W [34].",
    "We encode the NP contribution to these observables into a shift of the W mass, δm W, and into shifts of the W and Z couplings to SM fermions, described by means of the 3 × 3 matrices δg W ℓ, δg W q, δg Z f L (f = u, d, ν, e), and δg Zf R (f = u, d, e), defined as in appendix C.1 of ref.",
    "The same reference contains expressions for δm W and δg W,Z in terms of SMEFT WCs, thus providing a map to express all pole observables in terms of these coefficients.• We then consider tests of lepton flavor universality in leptonic and semi-leptonic τdecays."
